The U.K. Economy look strong month government unveiled budget fiscal 1987/88 Chancellor Exchequer Nigel Lawson said. He told Parliament "all indicator publish budget confirm anything do I suggest then." The budget unveiled March 17. "The PSBR (Public Sector Borrowing Requirement) low I forecast Budget. Inflation low I suggest ... (and) current account balance payment perform I predicted." The budget foresaw inflation ease 4.0 pct peak 4.5 pct. Lawson overall 1986/87 PSBR 4.0 billion stg. It low 3.3 billion stg. He project average GDP growth calendar 1987 3.0 pct 2.5 pct 1986. Lawson "output appear rise anything faster." Speaking House Commons debate "by register long period steady growth close 3.0 pct British economy know (Second World) War." The 1987/88 budget contain proposal cut basic rate taxation penny 27 penny pound. Lawson reaffirm government aim far cut standard rate "no 25p." He objective "should achieve." Turning policy propose political opposition party Lawson advocate Labour Party entail extra expenditure 34 billion stg. That "would require either double basic rate income tax treble standard rate (valued add tax) VAT" currently 15 pct. On value add tax Lawson note Conservative government promise 1984 extend VAT food. "Beyond incidence taxation determine budgetary need responsible government conceivably position" said. Labour MPs accuse Conservatives planning VAT increase essential consumer goods. Lawson reiterate belief reduction taxation produce high low revenue "thus lead scope far reduction taxation." Lawson "inheritance tax expect yield 50 pct real term Capital Transfer Tax 1978-79. The yield Capital Gains Tax forecast 80 pct high real term Stamp Duty 140 pct." He "the greatly increase yield Corporation Tax reflect greatly increase company profitability clearly connect reform Corporation Taxation I introduce 1984 brought rate tax company profit country low industrialise world." REUTER 